        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer557912297" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7967907295202448924">This novel reads as a chronicle, not only of Princess Jaya&apos;s life, but also of an India in transformation from the late 1800s up through the early years following Independence in 1947. <br/>I enjoyed reading this book and found Princess Jaya to be a remarkable woman. She weathers a lot of trying experiences and shows herself to be resilient. <br/><br/>The only fault I found with the novel, however, was in the sequencing of historical events. For instance, some of what the author stated about the placing of som</span>
  <span id="freeText7967907295202448924" style="display:none">This novel reads as a chronicle, not only of Princess Jaya's life, but also of an India in transformation from the late 1800s up through the early years following Independence in 1947. <br />I enjoyed reading this book and found Princess Jaya to be a remarkable woman. She weathers a lot of trying experiences and shows herself to be resilient. <br /><br />The only fault I found with the novel, however, was in the sequencing of historical events. For instance, some of what the author stated about the placing of some events during the First World War were not accurate. When I read a historical novel, I get a better appreciation for the novel when the historical events it describes are true and placed in the proper sequences. Perhaps for some other readers, that matters little. But for me, that took away from me giving this novel 5 stars. <br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="7967907295202448924" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
