        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1283597412" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13774863882145419590">A vivid confirmation of the depravity of human nature. Well written; sometimes compelling. India seems a land of millennia of multiple, contemporaneous and often overlapping upheavals, wars, injustices and violence at all levels of society. The reader is unable to relate well to any of the characters. The author uses an abundance of indian words, not all of which were in my unabridged dictionary, and the precise meanings of which were not always easily inferred from the context, and I felt a sma</span>
  <span id="freeText13774863882145419590" style="display:none">A vivid confirmation of the depravity of human nature. Well written; sometimes compelling. India seems a land of millennia of multiple, contemporaneous and often overlapping upheavals, wars, injustices and violence at all levels of society. The reader is unable to relate well to any of the characters. The author uses an abundance of indian words, not all of which were in my unabridged dictionary, and the precise meanings of which were not always easily inferred from the context, and I felt a small glossary would have been helpful. A map would also have been helpful as looking up place names on google often proved inexact, confusing, or fruitless.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13774863882145419590" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
